Speakers Section:
For each speaker, include the following information:

Luis Romero

Country of Origin: Peru

Educational Background: Master’s in Business Administration, Specialization in Digital Innovation

Full Biography: Luis Romero is a renowned expert in digital transformation with over 15 years of experience leading technological innovation projects in multinational companies. He is currently a consultant in digital transformation, helping organizations adapt to the digital age.

Topic: "The Role of Digital Transformation in Modern Organizations"


Clery Neyra

Country of Origin: Chile

Educational Background: Ph.D. in Artificial Intelligence, Specialization in Machine Learning

Full Biography: Clery Neyra has dedicated her career to the development and implementation of artificial intelligence solutions in various industries. With numerous publications and patents in the field, she is a recognized leader in the application of AI to enhance business processes.

Topic: "The Transformative Potential of Artificial Intelligence in Business"


Salim Ismail

Country of Origin: Canada

Educational Background: MBA, Specialization in Exponential Strategies

Full Biography: Salim Ismail is an internationally recognized author and strategist, known for his work on the concept of Exponential Organizations. He is the founder of several successful tech startups and has advised global companies on exponential growth strategies.

Topic: "How Exponential Organizations Are Redefining the Future of Business"
